# ==== Type Conversion ====

""""
Type Conversion is a process to convert the value type of any variable. There are 2 types of conversions. 
- Conversion --> is the automatic process to convert the type of any value. This is what python do on auto based.
- Casting --> is the process of manually convert the type of any value. Python is not gonna conveert it on auto-based.
"""

# ==== Conversion ====
a = 4  #integer value
b = 10.2  # float value
print(a + b) # while adding, so python auto convert your 'a + b' in to float because in float, we can store more data.

# ==== Casting ==== 
x = 2
y = float("2")
print(x + y)
print(type(y))

x = 2
y = int(2.9033423)
print(x + y)
print(type(y))
